carin-rtpbc-billing-unit-value-set


Defining URL:http://hl7.org/fhir/us/carin/ValueSet/rtpbc-billing-unit
Version:0.1.0
Name:CarinRtbpcBillingUnitValueSet
Status:Active
Title:CARIN RTPBC Billing Unit Value Set
Definition:

This value set contains the quantity unit of measure to be used when requesting predetermination of benefits for prescription-related products

Source Resource:XML / JSON / Turtle

Used in...

  • CARIN RTPBC Medication Request
  • CARIN RTPBC Request Using Claim
  • CARIN RTPBC Response Using ClaimResponse

Expansion

No Expansion for this valueset (not supported by Publication Tooling)


All codes are from the licensed NCPDP Unit of Measure (600-28) code set, maintained by the National Council for Prescription Drug Programs. See NCPDP Unit of Measure (600-28) (NamingSystem)

Concept examples

The up-to-date content of the NCPDP Unit of Measure (600-28) code set is available to NCPDP members.

However, a past version of the code set is publicly available in the AHRQ United States Health Information Knowledgebase (USHIK). Below is the full set of concepts from that public source.

CodeDisplay
EAEach
GMGram
MLMilliliter
